I know. It's weird.

00:24:47.120 --> 00:24:48.420
I mean, it's funny.

00:24:48.420 --> 00:24:51.020
There's a part in the book where
Obe turns around to his father

00:24:51.020 --> 00:24:52.570
and he says, plastics
ruined everything.

00:24:52.570 --> 00:24:54.190
And he goes, oh really,
plastics ruined everything.

00:24:54.190 --> 00:24:57.400
And then he opens up the fridge,
and he says, look at this.

00:24:57.400 --> 00:25:00.470
You milk, your yogurt,
your cheese, your meat.

00:25:00.470 --> 00:25:01.860
And he just starts
listing everything.

00:25:01.860 --> 00:25:05.190
Ketchup, your chocolate
syrup, this syrup,

00:25:05.190 --> 00:25:07.160
all these -- Everything's
in plastic.

00:25:07.160 --> 00:25:09.090
So it's not doing you -- And
look at the whole fridge.

00:25:09.090 --> 00:25:10.430
It's plastic.

00:25:10.430 --> 00:25:12.030
You know, it's not hurting you.

00:25:12.030 --> 00:25:14.650
And so, I think that's one of
those things that we have that sort

00:25:14.650 --> 00:25:16.480
of blinker vision on, you know.

00:25:16.480 --> 00:25:19.050
But yeah, it's annoying.

00:25:19.050 --> 00:25:21.170
I mean, I'd like to see, as
someone who goes to a lot

00:25:21.170 --> 00:25:24.070
of schools throughout
the year, I would really

00:25:24.070 --> 00:25:27.700 position:56%
